Doug Burgum released a video message on his first day in office , largely focusing on his stance on addressing the Dakota Access Pipeline situation while calling for federal resources and for a federal permit for a final river crossing to be issued . It was posted on his Facebook campaign page Thursday afternoon . An easement to allow drilling of the pipeline under the Missouri River will not be issued pending an environmental impact statement , according to the U.S. Army . He also pledged to meet with tribal leaders statewide in his first month in office .